    "framing": "Set-ConCA achieves 69.5% +/- 0.6pp cross-family transfer from Gemma-3 4B -> LLaMA-3 8B. Crucially, transferring from the larger model to the smaller model (LLaMA-3 8B -> Gemma-3 4B) achieves 59.6% +/- 3.5pp. The fact that bi-directional transfer works equally well supports the Platonic Representation Hypothesis: both models share an underlying semantic geometry, and one is not simply a subset of the other."
  },
