    "framing": "The correct comparison is among SPARSE + INTERPRETABLE methods: Set-ConCA, SAE-L1, and SAE-TopK. PCA and PCA-Threshold are non-sparse (L0\u22481.0) and non-interpretable \u2014 they are included as reconstruction upper bounds only. Among sparse methods, Set-ConCA achieves lower MSE than both SAE variants at equivalent sparsity (L0=25%). SAE-TopK is the fairest apples-to-apples comparison: same sparsity constraint (exactly k=32 active), pointwise architecture. In the verified rerun, pointwise SAE-TopK is higher on raw overlap transfer (EXP16), while Set-ConCA retains strong cross-family transfer/steering evidence and a competitive sparse reconstruction/transfer trade-off."
  },
