    "framing": "At alpha=0 (no intervention) the base similarity is 0.561 \u2014 high because all test anchors are topically related news. Set-ConCA (4B->8B) gains +9.8pp at alpha=10 while random collapses to 0.095. Weak-to-strong (1B concept -> 8B model) gains +10.7pp, demonstrating that even a much smaller model's concept vectors can effectively steer a larger model \u2014 supporting the universality of Set-ConCA representations. The divergence between Set-ConCA and random grows linearly with alpha, confirming directional precision (not merely magnitude effect)."
  },
